// Layer registry. Each entry describes a criterion, its data source, and how it renders.
// Sources verified against Askja's framework (r2) and the v1 specifications doc.
// Color ramps are chosen per data type — heat for climate, blue for water, etc.
// No composite scoring. No ranking. Each layer stands alone.
//
// `kind` controls how main.js wires the layer:
//   - 'raster-image'   → static PNG overlay (image source)
//   - 'point-symbol'   → GeoJSON points rendered as circles
//   - 'point-heatmap'  → GeoJSON points rendered as heatmap
//   - 'polygon-fill'   → GeoJSON polygons with property-driven fill
//   - null             → layer documented but data not yet wired (sidebar-only)

